            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long can a YouTube Short be?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>As of 2024, YouTube Shorts can be up to 3 minutes long, extended from the original 60-second limit. Videos must be filmed or uploaded in a vertical format (9:16 aspect ratio) to qualify as a Short.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do YouTube Shorts count toward watch hours for YPP?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Shorts views count separately. For YPP, Shorts views count toward the 10 million Shorts views threshold (for full YPP) or 3 million views threshold (for fan funding YPP). They do not count toward the 4,000 long-form watch hours threshold.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does posting YouTube Shorts hurt your long-form channel?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No — and YouTube has confirmed this officially. Shorts and long-form content are distributed by separate algorithms. Posting Shorts does not cannibalise long-form views. Most creators find that Shorts viewers convert to long-form subscribers over time.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How does YouTube Shorts monetisation work?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>YouTube pools ad revenue from the Shorts feed and distributes it to creators based on their proportional share of total Shorts views in each period. Creators keep 45% of their allocated revenue (vs 55% for long-form ad revenue). Shorts also support fan funding features (Super Thanks, channel memberships).</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
